Onboard vs. Ground Recording 2010-09-08T16:14:10.000Z The main video is recorded using a FatShark HD1.
The small video is recorded using a JXD990 directly connected to the video receiver. The Fatshark produces a much better video, despite the odd colors and the defocused lens.

The fatshark records 1280x720 8Mbit/s
The JXD990 records 704x448 4Mbit/s

both have a lousy encoder, I have seen 4Mbit/s videos that looked magnitudes better.

Maybe I will go for the GOPRO HERO HD.

Update: the HD1 is now broken, due to its bad construction, I now use the GoPro HD which is MUCH better. http://b.vimeocdn.com/ts/881/223/88122376_640.jpg
